You can adjust the difficulty level. This can also
be set in the Corridor of Depravity.

\n<■Difficulty \C[11][Casual>Casual]\C[0]■: The lighting in the cave increases,
and certain events become easier.

\n<■Difficulty \C[3][Original]\C[0]■>This is the original difficulty level. This world
is designed to ensnare Rui.

\n<Rui>...It's so dark, I can't see anything ahead at
all.

\n<About The Goblin>When you come into contact with a goblin, an
attack determination will occur.

\n<The Difference Upon Contact>If you make contact from behind, you can defeat
the goblin unscathed and unilaterally.

\n<Rui>That's a bit anticlimactic... I had the impression
they were quite vicious from what the guide
said...

\n<Rui>Well, easier is better. At this rate, it looks
like it'll be over quickly.

Goblin: Goblins are cunning and malicious
creatures. Even if they are about to be killed,
they won't stop if there's a young human female in
front of them.

\n<The Difference Upon Contact>If you make contact while facing the front,
there's a high chance you can defeat it without
consuming health...

\n<The Difference Upon Contact>If you are contacted from the side, Rui will
likely take damage from the goblin's attack.

\n<The Difference Upon Contact>If attacked from behind... the hunter's position
will be reversed in an instant.
